[{"question":"Do you want them to take it better?","answer":"No, I didn\u0027t want them to take it badly in the first place.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":32,"aSentId":33},{"question":"Too easy, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"I mean --","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":54,"aSentId":55},{"question":"That\u0027s what they call a home run, you know?","answer":"Yes, yes.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":57,"aSentId":58},{"question":"Do you have a moral code yourself?","answer":"Of course I do.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":81,"aSentId":82},{"question":"What\u0027s your litmus test?","answer":"Well, you can\u0027t.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":89,"aSentId":90},{"question":"But what are we meant to do?","answer":"For a very long time, you would never have imagined being in Hollywood.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":147,"aSentId":148},{"question":"What is the reality of Hollywood excess?","answer":"Well, I don\u0027t know about that.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":150,"aSentId":151},{"question":"Is it to not be famous too early?","answer":"Well, I think so.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":160,"aSentId":161},{"question":"Is it a lot easier, is my point, to be older and become famous?","answer":"Well, I think so.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":166,"aSentId":167},{"question":"It\u0027s the I can\u0027t believe my luck that I get up in the morning, have an idea, and I can start writing that idea and it will get made at the moment, you know?","answer":"What I can\u0027t believe is the way you look, because we all fell in love back in Britain with fat, chubby Ricky.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":175,"aSentId":176},{"question":"You didn\u0027t tell me then, though, did you?","answer":"No, I didn\u0027t.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":182,"aSentId":183},{"question":"How much weight have you lost?","answer":"Not much at all.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":195,"aSentId":196},{"question":"Hollywood smiley?","answer":"I got some free -- those things in a luxury lounge once, those -- I thought those made me gag.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":210,"aSentId":211},{"question":"What made you go on this vanity kick?","answer":"It wasn\u0027t a vanity kick.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":222,"aSentId":223},{"question":"Where would you be without that?","answer":"-- \"The death of a fight-useless chubby loser with -- who never cleans his teeth and stinks.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":247,"aSentId":248},{"question":"Do you get more groupies now?","answer":"I don\u0027t -- never got groupies.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":256,"aSentId":257},{"question":"Really?","answer":"No.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":258,"aSentId":259},{"question":"A svelte comedic auteur or as a chubby loser?","answer":"I think --","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":265,"aSentId":266},{"question":"History of television?","answer":"\"Seinfeld,\" lovely show.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":315,"aSentId":316},{"question":"You love Twitter, don\u0027t you?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":344,"aSentId":345},{"question":"Why do you like it so much?","answer":"I like it for lots of reasons.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":346,"aSentId":347},{"question":"What were you getting at?","answer":"Well, you know, as a comedian --","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":355,"aSentId":356},{"question":"-- you\u0027d fit in well looking like that?","answer":"Well, I thought I looked intellectual there --","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":362,"aSentId":363},{"question":"Always?","answer":"Of course.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":375,"aSentId":376},{"question":"How does your -- how does your atheism, which you\u0027re passionate about -- how does that play with your American audience, given that so many people in America are God-fearing people, and probably take exception to it?","answer":"Well, but they shouldn\u0027t.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":384,"aSentId":385},{"question":"Do I do that?","answer":"I don\u0027t think so.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":475,"aSentId":476},{"question":"Should we play you what Steve Carell said about you?","answer":"Yes, please.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":478,"aSentId":479},{"question":"Could you do what Ricky does?","answer":"Oh, not in a million years, no.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":487,"aSentId":488},{"question":"Why?","answer":"I think I would just get too skittish.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":489,"aSentId":490},{"question":"But you could play a Ricky Gervais character?","answer":"Perhaps, but to actually go in front of people and --","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":492,"aSentId":493},{"question":"-- you\u0027re all heart, aren\u0027t you?","answer":"That\u0027s right.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":505,"aSentId":506},{"question":"Do you like Steve Carell?","answer":"He\u0027s great.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":516,"aSentId":517},{"question":"What, with -- romantic love?","answer":"I\u0027m assuming women.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":548,"aSentId":549},{"question":"Once?","answer":"Once.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":556,"aSentId":557},{"question":"Why haven\u0027t you married her yet?","answer":"Well, we are, really.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":567,"aSentId":568},{"question":"Do you think you ever will?","answer":"Oh, I\u0027d never say never.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":572,"aSentId":573},{"question":"How do you show your romantic side?","answer":"I don\u0027t know.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":580,"aSentId":581},{"question":"It would be professional, really -- a moment in your life, what would it be?","answer":"There\u0027s loads of things whizzing through my head, but they\u0027re all from childhood.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":600,"aSentId":601},{"question":"Like what?","answer":"I just remembered one.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":602,"aSentId":603},{"question":"Steve, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Steve.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":650,"aSentId":651},{"question":"You appeared how many times on Johnny Carson?","answer":"About 140 times.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":662,"aSentId":663},{"question":"That has to be a record, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Yes, Bob Hope was the most, and I was the second most.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":664,"aSentId":665},{"question":"What was the idea?","answer":"Well, Charlie Hartsock and Vance DeGeneres, who are my partners at Carousel, had this idea to kind of trace the -- trace comedy in terms of generations and -- and how it cross-pollinates and sort of look to people\u0027s inspirations.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":687,"aSentId":688},{"question":"-- of superstar comedians, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":695,"aSentId":696},{"question":"How are you -- how are you billing it?","answer":"Well, I -- I don\u0027t know if it\u0027s a definitive history of comedy, but it is --","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":698,"aSentId":699},{"question":"On what makes people laugh?","answer":"It\u0027s unique in the way in which the comedians talk about what they do.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":700,"aSentId":701},{"question":"That happened between you and him?","answer":"That never happened.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":710,"aSentId":711},{"question":"Is there a stat -- when you all get together?","answer":"It\u0027s so subjective.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":723,"aSentId":724},{"question":"But biggest comedian wasn\u0027t your great burning ambition as a kid, was it?","answer":"No, not at all.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":778,"aSentId":779},{"question":"And if it\u0027s funny, then, you know?","answer":"Let\u0027s talk a little break, gents.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":801,"aSentId":802},{"question":"But you do -- do you thank God every day that these things happen?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":827,"aSentId":828},{"question":"It\u0027s a little bit like that, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"There -- there is no Moe and Larry here.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":838,"aSentId":839},{"question":"It will hide your own lack of character, right?","answer":"Correct.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":874,"aSentId":875},{"question":"Who -- if I could trap you both on a desert island separately and you could have one comedian with you to make you laugh for the rest of your days, who would you take?","answer":"I would take Alan Arkin.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":879,"aSentId":880},{"question":"Why?","answer":"Because he makes -- one-to-one, he makes me laugh more than anyone I\u0027ve ever met.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":881,"aSentId":882},{"question":"Really?","answer":"He is -- he\u0027s so dry and so acerbic, he just -- I love being around the man.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":883,"aSentId":884},{"question":"Who would you take?","answer":"I\u0027d probably take Groucho.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":885,"aSentId":886},{"question":"If you\u0027re honest, did you prefer life before, when you were more anonymous, or have you actually embraced the whole fame thing with great enthusiasm?","answer":"It\u0027s much, much better to be rich and famous.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":890,"aSentId":891},{"question":"I like to think it might have been, but you never know, you know?","answer":"It\u0027s a lot tougher to deal with, I think, if you get that kind of thing when you\u0027re younger.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":916,"aSentId":917},{"question":"Do you miss the character?","answer":"No.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":965,"aSentId":966},{"question":"Could you do what Ricky does?","answer":"Oh, not in a million years.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":969,"aSentId":970},{"question":"Why?","answer":"I think I would just get too skittish.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":972,"aSentId":973},{"question":"You\u0027ve got seven movies on the go, is that right, over the next two years?","answer":"And I\u0027m writing a symphony and I have a cooking show coming up.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":990,"aSentId":991},{"question":"Yes?","answer":"Did you ever imagine here you\u0027d be in Hollywood in your smart power suit, in the middle of a seven movie extravaganza --","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":993,"aSentId":994},{"question":"-- earning you, potentially, a billion dollars?","answer":"A billion dollars.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":996,"aSentId":997},{"question":"You must pinch yourself a bit, don\u0027t you?","answer":"I\u0027m always pinching myself.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":1001,"aSentId":1002},{"question":"You need to have had cigarettes burned on you for years, don\u0027t you, to be genuinely -- to make an audience laugh?","answer":"Exactly.","docId":"120304pmt","qSentId":1027,"aSentId":1028}]